data.description: Great opportunity to live in  a single family home with a yard in the highly desired Jefferson heights neighborhood. Steps to the Park and a short stroll to all  the southside shops and restaurants.  Qualified VA buyers have an opportunity to assume a  2.75 % loan. Great open floor plan with the master on the main, a courtyard and a detached rear double garage.  The seller's have installed a whole house water filter and  a reverse osmosis system for the kitchen sink and refrigerator.  Great curb appeal with the two covered porches.  When you walk inside you are greeted  with Hardwood floors , crown molding , soothing gray cabinetry in the kitchen along with granite countertops and a raised dining bar.  There is a half bath off of the great room .  The dining area has access to the rear grilling patio and back yard. The master suite is in the rear of the home and has a trey ceiling and a large walk in closet with 2 doors on either end , as well as a master bath with a dual  granite vanity, jetted tub and separate shower.  Upstairs has three spacious bedrooms, and one would make a great bonus room .  Gym flooring in fourth bedroom would be great for a toddlers room or kids playroom.  There is shared bath and laundry room upstairs as well. Move in ready with fresh paint , new tile on the balcony and zoysia sod in the front yard.
